{"title_page": "2008 Netball Superleague Grand Final", "text_new": "{{Shortdescription|Netball Superleague grand final}}\n{{Infobox football match\n| title = [[2007\u201308 Netball Superleague season|2008 Netball Superleague]] Grand Final\n| image = \n| image_size = 250\n| event = [[2007\u201308 Netball Superleague season]]\n| team1 = [[Galleria Mavericks]]\n| team1association = [[File:HertfordshireMavericksColours.png|20px]]\n| team1score = 43\n| team2 = <small>[[Loughborough Lightning (netball)|Loughborough Lightning]]</small>\n| team2association = [[File:LoughboroughLightningColours.png|20px]]\n| team2score = 39\n| details = ''Galleria Mavericks make their third successive grand final appearance and win their first Netball Superleague title.''  \n| date = 5 April 2008\n| stadium = [[K2 Leisure Centre]]\n| city = [[Crawley]]\n| woman_player1  = [[Amanda Newton (netball)|Amanda Newton]] <ref name=\"womensport080408\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.womensportreport.com/what-a-match-mavericks-def/wn/208|title=What a match! Mavericks def Loughborough Lightning in Super League Final|publisher=www.womensportreport.com|accessdate=3 April 2020|date=6 April 2008}}</ref>\n| referee = \n| attendance = \n| previous = [[2007 Netball Superleague Grand Final|2007]]\n| next = [[2009 Netball Superleague Grand Final|2009]]\n}}\n\nThe '''[[2007\u201308 Netball Superleague season|2008 Netball Superleague]] Grand Final''' featured [[Galleria Mavericks]] and [[Loughborough Lightning (netball)|Loughborough Lightning]]. Having played in both the [[2006 Netball Superleague Grand Final|2006]] and [[2007 Netball Superleague Grand Final|2007]] grand finals, this was Mavericks' third successive grand final appearance. It proved third time lucky for Mavericks who defeated Lightning 43\u201339.\n\nLightning were leading 21\u201314 at half time thanks to an outstanding shooting performance from 19-year-old [[Joanne Harten]]. However Mavericks, inspired by [[Louisa Brownfield]] and [[Karen Atkinson (netball)|Karen Atkinson]], subsequently began to create more shooting opportunities.  Mavericks defence \u2013 [[Amanda Newton (netball)|Amanda Newton]], Clare Elsley and Naomi Siddall \u2013 also played a vital part in a second half fight back. By the end of the third quarter, Mavericks had reduced Lightning's lead to 28\u201331. During the final quarter Mavericks drew level at 34\u201334, before pulling ahead by six goals thanks to clinical finishing from Brownfield and Michelle Hall. Harten scored four goals to help keep Lightning in touch before three goals from Brownfield secured the title for Mavericks. <ref name=\"womensport080408\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.womensportreport.com/what-a-match-mavericks-def/wn/208|title=What a match! Mavericks def Loughborough Lightning in Super League Final|publisher=www.womensportreport.com|accessdate=3 April 2020|date=6 April 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"express050408\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.express.co.uk/netball/40383/Superleague-victory-for-Mavericks|title=Superleague victory for Mavericks|publisher=www.express.co.uk|accessdate=5 April 2020|date=5 April 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"whtimes060408\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.whtimes.co.uk/sport/third-time-lucky-for-magnificent-mavericks-1-15894|title=Third time lucky for magnificent Mavericks|publisher=www.whtimes.co.uk|accessdate=3 February 2020|date=6 April 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"lewes050408\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.lewesnetballclub.co.uk/pg_super_league.html|title=Super leauge &#91;sic&#93; final 5th April 2008|publisher=www.lewesnetballclub.co.uk|accessdate=3 April 2020|date=5 April 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"sportsister080408\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sportsister.com/2008/04/08/mavericks-win-netball-superleague-final/|title=Mavericks win Netball Superleague final|publisher=www.sportsister.com|accessdate=4 February 2020|date=8 April 2008}}</ref>\n\n==Route to the Final==\n{{see|2007\u201308 Netball Superleague season}}\n\n==Match summary==\n{{netballbox\n | bg         = #E