ar]] award at [[Mirchi Music Awards]] [[8th Mirchi Music Awards|2015]] for \"Moh Moh Ke Dhaage\" from ''[[Dum Laga Ke Haisha]]''\n* Nominated for [[Filmfare Award for Best Lyricist|Best Lyricist at 61st Filmfare Awards]] 2016\n* Nominated for Best Raaga-based song for ''Aayi Bahaar'' of ''[[Ankhon Dekhi]]'' at the [[Mirchi Music Awards]] [[7th Mirchi Music Awards|2014]]\n* Nominated for Best Lyrics for ''Womaniya'' of ''[[Gangs of Wasseypur \u2013 Part 1]]'' at the [[Apsara Film & Television Producers Guild Award]] 2013\n* Awarded for Best Screenplay and Best Lyrics for song \"Tu Kisi rail si\" from movie ''Masaan'' at the Stardust Award 2015.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{National Film Award Best Lyrics}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Grover, Varun}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Punjabi people]]\n[[Category:Indian male comedians]]\n[[Category:Indian male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:People from Mandi district]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from Himachal Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Indian television writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male writers]]\n[[Category:Best Lyrics National Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:Male television writers]]\n[[Category:Novelists from Himachal Pradesh]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=March 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n{{Infobo\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1980|1|26}}\n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| birth_plac         = [[Sundernagar]], [[Himachal Pradesh]], India\n| occupation         = [[Screenwriter]], [[lyricist]], [[Film director|director]], [[stand-up comedian]]\n| yearsactive        = 2004-2005\n| notable_works      = [[Masaan]], [[Udta Punjab]], [[Dum Laga Ke Haisha]], [[Sacred Games (TV series)|Sacred Games]]\n| nationality        = [[India]]n\n| alma_mater         = [[Indian Institute of Technology (BHU) Varanasi]]\n| spouse             = \n}}\n\n'''Varun Grover''' (born 26 January 1980) is an India[[Intellectual|inker]]. He won the award for Best Lyricist at the 63rd [[National Film Awards]] in 2015.<ref name=\"63rdawardPDF\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dff.nic.in/writereaddata/Winners_of_63rd_NFA_2015.pdf|title=63rd National Film Awards|publisher=[[Directorate of Film Festivals]]|accessdate=13 February 2018|format=PDF}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Pal|first1=Divya|title=National Award winning lyricist Varun Grover recalls initial reactions to 'Moh Moh Ke Dhaage'|url=http://www.news18.com/news/movies/bahut-achcha-hai-par-slow-hai-national-award-winning-lyricist-varun-grover-recalls-initial-reactions-to-moh-moh-ke-dhaage-1222145.html|accessdate=13 February 2018|date=28 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Varun Grover (Civil 2003) wins award as Best Lyricist at 63rd National Film Awards 2016|url=http://www.itbhuglobal.org/chronicle/archives/2016/03/varun_grover_ci_1.php|accessdate=13 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nGrover was born in [[Sundernagar]], [[Himachal Pradesh]], to a school-teacher mother and army engineer father. His family is [[Punjabi people|Punjabi]].<ref>Akshay Manwani (24 July 2016), [https://scroll.in/reel/812351/varun-grover-interview-the-lack-of-respect-for-writers-stays-with-you-but-also-fuels-you \"Varun Grover interview: \u2018The lack of respect for writers stays with you, but also fuels you\u2019\"], ''[[Scroll.in]]''. Retrieved 20 March 2020.</ref> He spent his initial years in Sundernagar and [[Dehradun]], [[Uttarakhand]], before moving to [[Lucknow]], [[Uttar Pradesh]] for his adolescent years. He studied civil engineering at [[Indian Institute of Technology (BHU) Varanasi]], graduating in 2003.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/brutal-censors-give-another-route-to-creativity-masaan-writer-varun-grover/|title=Brutal censors give another route to creativity: \u2018Masaan\u2019 writer Varun Grover|date=2015-10-07|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2018-01-19|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Liberal in his thoughts |url=http://dailypost.in/lifestyle/fashion-and-beauty/52886-liberal-in-his-thoughts | agency=Daily Post India | accessdate=2015-11-25 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thebetterindia.com/92124/varun-grover-interview-comedy-songwriter-scrip-writer/|title=EXCLUSIVE: Varun Grover on His Journey, the Film Industry, & Sexism in Standup Comedy|date=2017-03-20|work=The Better India|access-date=2018-01-19|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.livemint.com/Leisure/VXp7QpToHxvptmcOU9ZCyH/Masaan-man-Varun-Grovers-journey-A-civil-engineer-turned-B.html|title=Masaan man Varun Grover\u2019s journey: A civil engineer turned Bollywood scriptwriter|last=Jha|first=Lata|date=2015-08-05|work=livemint.com|access-date=2018-08-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/neeraj-ghaywan-varun-grover-to-donate-national-award-prize-money-to-farmers-2784161/|title=Neeraj Ghaywan, Varun Grover to donate National Award prize money to farmers|date=2016-05-04|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2018-01-19|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/VXp7QpToHxvptmcOU9ZCyH/Masaan-man-Varun-Grovers-journey-A-civil-engineer-turned-B.html|title=Masaan man Varun Grover\u2019s journey: A civil engineer turned Bollywood scriptwriter|first=Lata|last=Jha|date=5 August 2015|publisher=Mint}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/07/06/arts/television/sacred-games-netflix-review.html |title=Review: The Criminal Life in Mumbai in \u2018Sacred Games\u2019 |date=6 July 2018 |work=The New York Times |access-date=15 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/web-series/the-devil-of-the-details-5239759/ |title=Sacred Games review: The Devil of the Details |date=30 June 2018 |work=The Indian Express |access-date=15 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Collaboration in the Independent music space ==\nIn 2017 Varun Grover released Beete Dino Ke Geet<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/people-writer-comedian-varun-grover-discusses-new-collaboration-indie-space-lifestyle/18284165 |title=Indian music and cinema are tough nuts to crack: Varun Grover |website=mid-day.com |date=27 May 2017}}</ref> - a song in collaboration with US-based producer [[Krishna Chetan]].\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| ''[[Sandeep Aur Pinky Faraar]]'' || 2020 || Writer\n|-\n|''[[Sonchiriya]]''\n|2019\n| rowspan=\"8\" |Lyricist <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/buzz/sacred-games-makers-talk-about-their-favourite-character-criticism-and-first-pirated-show-in-reddit-ama-1826687.html|title='Sacred Games' Makers Talk About Their Favourite Character, Criticism, and First Pirated Show in Reddit AMA|work=News18|access-date=2018-09-12}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Sui Dhaaga]]''\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2018\n|-\n| ''[[Kaala (2018 film)|Kaala]]''\n|-\n| ''[[Newton (film)|Newton]]'' || 2017 <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/padmaavat-varun-grover-comedy-sanjay-leela-bhansali-deepika-padukone-karni-sena/191770|title=Before watching Padmaavat, check out comedian Varun Grover's hilarious take on the film|access-date=2018-08-02|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Udta Punjab]]'' \n|rowspan=\"4\"|2016 <ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-varun-grover-lyricist-of-many-phantom-films-slams-vikas-bahl-for-sexually-abusing-a-female-employee-2396304|title=Varun Grover, lyricist of many Phantom films, SLAMS Vikas Bahl for sexually abusing a female employee!|date=2017-04-11|work=dna|access-date=2018-08-02|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Raman Raghav 2.0]]''<ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n| ''[[Fan (film)|Fan]]''\n|-\n| ''[[Zubaan]]''\n|-\n| ''[[Fly Away S